 in engineering in       She was the first woman to earn each of these degrees from the UIC College of Engineering She will return to campus Dec Holmes      worked at Sargent   Lundy  a Chicago engineering firm serving the power industry  from      to       She helped develop computer programs used to determine the magnitude and effects of loads on structures in nuclear and fossil fuel plants caused by earthquakes  She also supervised work on computer programs for soil structure interactions  the generation of response spectra  and analysis of HVAC hangers and piping systems Holmes insists that engineering is a great profession for women  typical choices for women were general liberal arts  teaching  home economics  journalism  and for the very daring  business or science  We expected to work a few years and get married and then stay home with the children  but many of us soon discovered that we would be working for some time of our lives  If only more women realized what a challenging and financially rewarding career engineering provides  I think there would be more women in this field Holmes has been an active member of Engineers Without Borders for many years  and has traveled to Guatemala and Honduras to help develop bridges and sanitation systems  She established the Nancy Anderson Holmes scholarship in      in memory of her aunt  which benefits UIC civil engineering students  She received the Legacy Alumni Achievement Award from the UIC College of Engineering in November Holmes lives in Oak Park with her husband  Tom  They have three children     grandchildren and two great grandchildren  n nContact n nSharon Parmet n t t t t t t t             nsparmet uic edu n n n nCategories n nAlumni  Campus  n Contact  nSharon Parmet n t t t t t t t             nsparmet uic edu n Sharon Parmet sparmet uic edu Categories  nAlumni  Campus  Alumni Campus Topics alumni  commencement  engineering  Golden Grad  graduation  women in engineering alumni commencement engineering Go